CHOCOLATE + MARSHMALLOWS + PEANUT BUTTER + MATZAH🍫🤤🥜UJA’s #MatzahChallenge is back and I am so excited to be part of it.💙This year, it’s all about showing Jewish pride and standing up to anti-Jewish hatred!🇮🇱I decided to make homemade kosher Matzah Mallomars with a little spin.🌀🥜 What’s so great about this recipe is that you really don’t have to measure anything AND it’s only 5 ingredients, 4 if you don’t count olive oil AND all you have to do is put everything together and place it all in the refrigerator for just 15 minutes and you can eat!!✡️

💙Ingredients:
-Matzah (duh)
-Kosher Marshmallows
-Chunky Peanut Butter
-Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips 
-Olive Oil (optional, to smooth out the melted chocolate)

The season finale of @pumprules is this week and I am schvitzing just thinking about it-I am so excited!😬Obviously, I had to celebrate my birthday at @vanderpumpparis in Las Vegas this past weekend, and I’ll be honest, though the ambience is lovely and the staff are incredibly kind and friendly, I wouldn’t jump through hoops to go back…Don’t get me wrong, I am a huge fan of Lisa Vanderpump and the cast of Vanderpump Rules, but this just wasn’t it..🤷🏻‍♀️I’ll always be a fan though!⭐️Rating below!!

*Cocktails - 8/10 (Instagrammable & Strong)
*Goat Cheese Cakes - 2/10 
*Filet Mignon - 6/10 (Tasty, but not worth the hour+ wait)
*Gruyere Fries - 3/10 (If you like spice, get these, but they didn’t arrive until 30 minutes after our entrees…)
*Creme Brûlée Beignets - 10/10 (DELICIOUS)😋
